PN,41201
SC,0001
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F412A1782907570
OL,3,CThe pilgrimage to the Battle of the
OL,4,CSomme
OL,6,FThey called it "The Great War to end
OL,7,Fall wars".
OL,9,FActually, there was nothing great
OL,10,Fabout it.
OL,12,FThe name reflected its sheer scale,
OL,13,Funprecedented global reach, and the
OL,14,Fcatastrophic loss of life.
OL,16,FThey were unmatched in history, up to
OL,17,Fthat time.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G1/20
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,413,410,140,120,000,100
PN,41202
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F412A1782907570
OL,3,CThe pilgrimage to the Battle of the
OL,4,CSomme
OL,6,FWithout the events of 1914-18, there
OL,7,Fwould not have been communism in
OL,8,FRussia, fascism in Germany in the
OL,9,F1930s, and The Second World War,
OL,10,Fitself.
OL,12,FThat, in turn, led to The Cold War,
OL,13,FKorea, the Cuban Missile Crisis,
OL,14,FVietnam, and the Middle East.
OL,16,FMuch closer to home, it raises the
OL,17,Fquestion about the political division
OL,18,Fof Ireland.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G2/20
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,413,410,140,120,000,100
PN,41203
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F412A1782907570
OL,3,CThe pilgrimage to the Battle of the
OL,4,CSomme
OL,6,FTo some, the First World War must
OL,7,Fappear to be ancient history. But,
OL,8,Fover 100 years after it ended, we are
OL,9,Fstill living with the echoes of that
OL,10,Ftime.
OL,12,FThe "Great War" has always fascinated
OL,13,Fme.
OL,15,FMy grand uncle, Donald Clark, was a
OL,16,Fsoldier in the 14th Battalion Royal
OL,17,FIrish Rifles.
OL,19,FHe was a member of the YCV. He fought
OL,20,Fat the Somme, in July 1916. He
OL,21,Fsurvived!
OL,26,@tD@EOUtD@OO]
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G3/20
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,413,410,140,120,000,100
PN,41204
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F412A1782907570
OL,3,CThe pilgrimage to the Battle of the
OL,4,CSomme
OL,6,FHe didn't die until 1980 ` living long
OL,7,Fenough to know that it was not "The
OL,8,FGreat War to end all wars".
OL,10,FMy interest in the period is two-fold.
OL,11,FHistory has always fascinated me. The
OL,12,FFirst World War brought that history
OL,13,Finto sharp focus ` particularly on the
OL,14,Fisland of Ireland.
OL,16,FThe Third Home Rule Act had just
OL,17,Fbecome law in 1914. It permitted Irish
OL,18,Fself-government within the British
OL,19,FEmpire, rather than full independence
OL,20,For total separation from the UK.
OL,26,@oD@`OU
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G4/20
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,413,410,140,120,000,100
PN,41205
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F412A1782907570
OL,3,CThe pilgrimage to the Battle of the
OL,4,CSomme
OL,6,FIt sought to establish a devolved
OL,7,Fparliament in Dublin to manage local
OL,8,Fdomestic affairs, while Westminster
OL,9,Fretained overall control.
OL,11,FThis prospect alarmed unionists.
OL,13,FAn Irish Parliament with a Catholic
OL,14,Fnationalist majority frightened
OL,15,FProtestants in Ulster. Led by Sir
OL,16,FEdward Carson,
OL,18,FUnionists formed the Ulster Volunteer
OL,19,FForce to resist Home Rule by force.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G5/20
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,413,410,140,120,000,100
PN,41206
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F412A1782907570
OL,3,CThe pilgrimage to the Battle of the
OL,4,CSomme
OL,6,FHowever, escalating tensions in
OL,7,FEurope, and the outbreak of war in
OL,8,F1914, led to Home Rule being put on
OL,9,Fhold.
OL,11,FThis resulted in many nationalists and
OL,12,Funionists fighting for different
OL,13,Fpolitical reasons. But they could find
OL,14,Fcommon cause in fighting for the
OL,15,FBritish.
OL,17,FUnionists fought to demonstrate their
OL,18,Floyalty to the Crown and secure
OL,19,FUlster's place in the UK. Nationalists
OL,20,Ffought to secure the promised Home
OL,21,FRule.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G6/20
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,413,410,140,120,000,100
PN,41207
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F412A1782907570
OL,3,CThe pilgrimage to the Battle of the
OL,4,CSomme
OL,6,FWhile both groups enlisted in the
OL,7,FBritish Army, they did so to achieve
OL,8,Fopposing political goals at home. My
OL,9,Fgrand uncle, Donald, was a Belfast
OL,10,Fprotestant, and a unionist.
OL,12,FHis brother, my grandfather, signed
OL,13,Fthe Ulster Covenant.
OL,15,FHowever, German bullets did not
OL,16,Fdistinguish between Catholic and
OL,17,FProtestant; unionist or nationalist.
OL,18,FThe war exacted a high price in all
OL,19,Fhuman life.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G7/20
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,413,410,140,120,000,100
PN,41208
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F412A1782907570
OL,3,CThe pilgrimage to the Battle of the
OL,4,CSomme
OL,6,FMillions died, and the vast majority
OL,7,Fof the British were buried where they
OL,8,Ffell. Too many do not have a grave, or
OL,9,Fa name.
OL,11,FThe Imperial War Graves Commission was
OL,12,Festablished in 1917.
OL,14,FIt became The Commonwealth War Graves
OL,15,FCommission in 1960, to better reflect
OL,16,Fthe Commonwealth of Nations.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G8/20
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,413,410,140,120,000,100
PN,41209
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F412A1782907570
OL,3,CThe pilgrimage to the Battle of the
OL,4,CSomme
OL,6,FOriginally, there had been an
OL,7,Fexpectation that people would only
OL,8,Fvisit these cemeteries, until that
OL,9,Fgeneration became too frail to travel,
OL,10,For died.
OL,12,FBut, the world has changed out of all
OL,13,Frecognition. Comparatively easy travel
OL,14,F- and a growing interest from future
OL,15,Fgenerations ` now means that more
OL,16,Fpeople than ever are visiting these
OL,17,Fcemeteries and memorials.
OL,19,FBut going to see the war graves is not
OL,20,Fdark tourism. It is a pilgrimage.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G9/20
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,413,410,140,120,000,100
PN,41210
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F412A1782907570
OL,3,CThe pilgrimage to the Battle of the
OL,4,CSomme
OL,6,FMillions of people travel annually to
OL,7,Fthese sites and cemeteries to pay
OL,8,Frespects, explore family history, and
OL,9,Flearn about the sacrifices made during
OL,10,Fwar.
OL,12,FIn my job, I have been to the
OL,13,Fbattlefields many times. I never tire
OL,14,Fof going to these "theatres of war".
OL,16,FI have just returned from a journey to
OL,17,Fnorthern France.
OL,19,FThis time I was accompanied by
OL,20,Fcolleagues from UTV.
OL,26,@vD@SOU
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}           G10/20
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,413,410,140,120,000,100
PN,41211
SC,0011
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F412A1782907570
OL,3,CThe pilgrimage to the Battle of the
OL,4,CSomme
OL,6,FOur interest is fuelled by more than
OL,7,Four jobs. So, accompanied by our head
OL,8,Fof security, Colin Barbour, and two
OL,9,Fcameramen, John Vennard, and Alan
OL,10,FDeans, we spent a week walking-the-
OL,11,Fwalk, with surprising results.
OL,13,FYes, our main interest was the Battle
OL,14,Fof the Somme. July 1st, 1916 remains
OL,15,Fthe bloodiest day in the history of
OL,16,Fthe Army.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}           G11/20
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,413,410,140,120,000,100
PN,41212
SC,0012
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F412A1782907570
OL,3,CThe pilgrimage to the Battle of the
OL,4,CSomme
OL,6,FOur go-to locations included the huge
OL,7,FMemorial to the Missing at Thiepval,
OL,8,Fand the nearby Ulster Tower. That was
OL,9,Fone of the first monuments to be
OL,10,Ferected on the Western Front.
OL,12,FOur journey took us to the German War
OL,13,FCemetery at Fricourt. I have always
OL,14,Ffelt it important to pay respects at
OL,15,Fall cemeteries.
OL,17,FThe poppy wreaths tell their own
OL,18,Fstory... we weren't the only visitors
OL,19,Ffrom the UK.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}           G12/20
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,413,410,140,120,000,100
PN,41213
SC,0013
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F412A1782907570
OL,3,CThe pilgrimage to the Battle of the
OL,4,CSomme
OL,6,FWe also travelled to Flanders, in
OL,7,FBelgium. At the Menin Gate in Ieper/
OL,8,FYpres there is a solemn act of
OL,9,Fremembrance every evening at 8pm, when
OL,10,FThe Last Post is sounded.
OL,12,FWe found ourselves in the company of
OL,13,FGreengairs Thistle Flute Band, from
OL,14,FScotland. They even dressed for the
OL,15,Foccasion, wearing the traditional
OL,16,FTommy uniform, from the period.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}           G13/20
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,413,410,140,120,000,100
PN,41214
SC,0014
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F412A1782907570
OL,3,CThe pilgrimage to the Battle of the
OL,4,CSomme
OL,6,FAlan Deans knew he had a relation
OL,7,Fburied in France, who'd died in the
OL,8,FFirst World War. Albert Grainger
OL,9,Fworshipped at Agnes Street
OL,10,FPresbyterian Church, off the Shankill
OL,11,FRoad.
OL,13,FInterestingly, he joined the Black
OL,14,FWatch, rather than an Irish regiment.
OL,16,FHe died in October 1916, later in the
OL,17,FSomme campaign; and is buried at
OL,18,FDernancourt Communal Cemetery
OL,19,FExtension, near the town of Albert. He
OL,20,Fwas 19.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}           G14/20
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,413,410,140,120,000,100
PN,41215
SC,0015
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F412A1782907570
OL,3,CThe pilgrimage to the Battle of the
OL,4,CSomme
OL,6,FThe Pipers' Memorial in the village of
OL,7,FLongueval, also on the Somme, is a
OL,8,Fstriking, all-white monument,
OL,9,Fdedicated to the thousands of pipers
OL,10,Facross all Allied units and
OL,11,Fnationalities who served and fell
OL,12,Fduring the Great War.
OL,14,FMany of them bravely played troops
OL,15,Fover the top, despite shelling and
OL,16,Fgunfire.
OL,18,FWhile paying our respects, we were
OL,19,Fapproached by an Englishman who
OL,20,Finformed us of a burial taking place
OL,21,Fin a nearby Commonwealth War Cemetery.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}           G15/20
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,413,410,140,120,000,100
PN,41216
SC,0016
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F412A1782907570
OL,3,CThe pilgrimage to the Battle of the
OL,4,CSomme
OL,6,FSquadron Leader George Fidler flew a
OL,7,FHurricane and was shot down on May
OL,8,F19th, 1940, as the Allies were
OL,9,Fretreating towards Dunkirk.
OL,11,FHe had no known grave until now. His
OL,12,Fremains were discovered during an
OL,13,Fexcavation.
OL,15,FHe was buried with full military
OL,16,Fhonours, at London Cemetery.
OL,18,FForced back by relentless pressure,
OL,19,Fthe Allied forces retreated into a
OL,20,Fshrinking pocket around Dunkirk.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}           G16/20
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,413,410,140,120,000,100
PN,41217
SC,0017
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F412A1782907570
OL,3,CThe pilgrimage to the Battle of the
OL,4,CSomme
OL,6,FJohn Vennard had a great uncle who
OL,7,Fserved in The Irish Guards.
OL,9,FThomas Henry Mawhinney survived, but
OL,10,Fmany of his colleagues did not. He was
OL,11,Fawarded the Military Medal.
OL,13,FHis war ended in North Africa in 1943.
OL,14,FHe's buried in La Reunion War Cemetery
OL,15,Fin Algeria.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}           G17/20
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,413,410,140,120,000,100
PN,41218
SC,0018
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F412A1782907570
OL,3,CThe pilgrimage to the Battle of the
OL,4,CSomme
OL,6,FBut, finally, I return to the main
OL,7,Freason for our journey ` The Somme. On
OL,8,Fa previous visit to the Thiepval
OL,9,FMemorial I came across a message on a
OL,10,Fpoppy wreath which read ` "...and
OL,11,Fdon't forget the animals."
OL,13,FHorses and mules were essential for
OL,14,Fmoving troops, hauling heavy
OL,15,Fartillery, and bringing up food and
OL,16,Fammunition through the mud.
OL,18,FIn the days before mass mechanisation,
OL,19,Fthey were the Army's logistical
OL,20,Fbackbone.
OL,26,@rD@[OUsD@ZO]
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}           G18/20
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,413,410,140,120,000,100
PN,41219
SC,0019
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F412A1782907570
OL,3,CThe pilgrimage to the Battle of the
OL,4,CSomme
OL,6,FMillions died or disappeared during
OL,7,FThe Great War. They knew danger; they
OL,8,Fknew fear.
OL,10,FThe animals could tell when a shell
OL,11,Fwas coming close and if, when halted,
OL,12,Fthe horses heard the whine of an
OL,13,Fapproaching salvo, they would tremble
OL,14,Fand sidle closer to their drivers,
OL,15,Fburying their muzzles into the men's
OL,16,Fchests.
OL,18,FWe honour their memory, with this
OL,19,Fdeeply moving epitaph... They had no
OL,20,Fchoice.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}           G19/20
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
